      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "COMPTON STELLA (3) has a strong record this track and trip with four wins and four placings from eight starts. Comes off a (23.40) win last time, scoring by a neck in a TG1-4W over 400m at this track. With a clean break looks hard to beat. MAJOR QUEEN (1) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when second (22.95) at this track over 400m. Yet to score from this box but has never missed the frame in two starts. Well-placed to take this out. COMPTON BOWIE (5) was strong over this course and distance last time despite filling the minors, finishing 6 lengths behind Big Boy Jett in 23.30 and recording a new PB here. Expected to feature again. OPAL LIMES (7) gets a chance to redeem an unplaced effort here last start.",
